Instructions for building and running migration scripts/programs
----------------------------------------------------------------

To migrate a PDF, install LHAPDF5 (including the Python module) and call e.g.

./creategrids CT10.LHgrid

This will create the .info set metadata file and .lha grid data files in a (new)
CT10 directory.

To test querying and writing the new PDFs, one member at a time, build the
testpdf program, e.g.:

g++ testpdf.cc -I$HOME/heplocal/include -L$HOME/heplocal/lib -lLHAPDF -lboost_filesystem -lboost_system -o testpdf

and run it with set and member ID as arguments, making sure to specify the paths
to the lhapdf.conf and current dir:

LHAPDF_DATA_PATH=$PWD ./testpdf CT10 0

The cmppdfs script can be used to numerically compare dumped-out PDF values as written by testpdf:

./cmppdfs CT10-lha5/CT10_0_21.dat CT10-lha6/CT10_0_21.dat -o CT10_0_21_5vs6.dat

(the optional output file is written in the same format as the PDF dumps, to
allow the differences to be visualised with the same code as the PDF value
dumps)

g++ dumpv5.cc -o dumpv5 `lhapdf-config --cppflags -cxxflags --ldflags --libs`
g++ dumpv6.cc -o dumpv6 `lhapdf-config --cppflags -cxxflags --ldflags --libs`
LHAPDF_DATA_PATH=$PWD ./dumpv6 CT10 0
./dumpv5 CT10.LHgrid 0
